==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grangerism
<hw>Gran"ger*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from
the <person>Rev. James <etsep>Granger</etsep></person>, whose
⟦ldquo⟧Biographical History of England⟦rdquo⟧ (1769) was a favorite book
for illustration in this manner.]</ety> <def>The practice of
illustrating a particular book by engravings collected from other
books.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grangerite</ent>⟦br⟧
